  "response": "To start commodity trading, follow these steps:\n\n1. Education\n- Learn about commodity markets\n- Understand different commodity types\n- Study trading strategies\n- Read financial news and market reports\n\n2. Choose a Trading Method\n- Futures contracts\n- Options\n- ETFs\n- Physical commodities\n- Commodity-related stocks\n\n3. Select a Broker\n- Open a trading account\n- Ensure the broker offers commodity trading\n- Compare commission rates\n- Check platform features\n\n4. Pick Commodities to Trade\n- Agricultural products\n- Energy (oil, natural gas)\n- Metals (gold, silver)\n- Decide based on your interest and research\n\n5. Risk Management\n- Set trading limits\n- Use stop-loss orders\n- Start with small investments\n- Diversify your portfolio\n\n6. Trading Platforms\n- Use online trading platforms\n- Learn technical analysis tools\n- Practice with demo accounts\n\n7. Required Capital\n- Minimum investment varies\n- Futures trading typically requires more capital\n- Start with amount you can afford to lose\n\n8. Continuous Learning\n- Stay updated on market trends\n- Monitor global economic conditions\n- Attend webinars and workshops\n\n9. Consider Consulting a Financial Advisor\n\nRemember: Commodity trading involves significant risk, so proceed cautiously.",
